Messages of innocence dominated speeches as family and friends of former Nairobi town clerk, the late John Gakuo converged at the All Saints Cathedral in Nairobi for a memorial service ahead of his burial in Ol kalou, Nyandarua county Friday. Gakuo’s family vowed to fight to the bitter end until his name is cleared of the corruption allegations that saw sentenced to a 3year jail term that claimed his life while still in custody.  